title: Selivanov, Volgograd Oblast
text:
Selivanov (Russian: Селиванов) is a rural locality (a khutor) in Zakharovskoye Rural Settlement, Kletsky District, Volgograd Oblast, Russia. The population was 227 as of 2010. There are 5 streets.


== Geography ==
The village is located on the bank of the Kurtlak River.
